contents.name: Fresh Yogurt
contents.description: Our yogurts are made in the hand-crafted, artisanal European tradition, w/ a California twist. We hand-pour local, clover organic milk into our small batch pasteurizer to make our non-fat, 2% & whole milk fresh yogurts. Our fresh yogurt is just organic milk & probiotic culture – we don't use additives, preservatives, gelatins, colorings or even sugar. Once you try our delicious fresh yogurts w/ our carefully selected toppings, or take away a pint to enjoy at home, you'll never want to get yogurt from the grocery store again!

contents.name: Frozen Yogurt
contents.description: Our all natural frozen yogurt is made on-site using our fresh yogurt as a base. You can choose from three supremely crave able flavors: fat-free natural, 98% fat free valrhona chocolate & 99% fat free, lactose-free soy. And, yes, our probiotic culture survives the freezing process, so you'll enjoy all the same health benefits as you would w/ our fresh yogurt.

contents.name: Oatmeal & Baked Goods
contents.description: If you're craving a healthy breakfast or snack besides yogurt, we also offer a slow-cooked steel cut oatmeal, & a variety of baked goods hand-made by a good friend of ours, who shares our commitment to using high-quality ingredients & minimizing sugar & fat.

contents.name: Blue Bottle Organic Coffee
contents.description: We also proudly serve coffee roasted by blue bottle, an organic Oakland micro-roaster that is consistently voted among the best in the country.

contents.text: We are passionate about health, great food & great quality ingredients. We hope you & your family enjoy your fraiche treats, & that you leave our cafe a little happier & healthier.
Our savory free-range chicken is brined for 24 hours, marinated in our special blend of herbs & spices, then roasted golden-brown until tender & juicy in our rotisserie oven.

contents.description: Brown rice is every weight watcher's dream food. It is rich in fiber. Brown has soluble fiber like the white rice; in addition, it has insoluble fiber on the outside. The soluble fibers slow the rate at which food leaves the stomach & promote a sense of satiety, or fullness, after a meal. This helps to prevent overeating & weight gain Rich w/ b-vitamins, niacin, potassium, manganese, & magenesium.

contents.name: Rice Noodles

They come in wide or thin shapes, as brown or white noodles & in fresh or dried form.Rich w/ dietery fiber, b-vitamins, iron, & selenium.

Organic Golden Tip Black Tea
contents.description: Organic Golden Tip is a delightfully fruity & flavorful new organic black tea that's so delicious you'll want to serve it to your most honored guests, yet affordable enough to drink every day. Made from young leaves plus abundant furry tips oxidized to a brilliant gold, this handsome tea immediately impresses w/ its rich, fruity nose. It infuses to a deep amber liquor marked by notes of ripe fruit w/ tantalizing hints of smoke, & ends w/ a sweet, crisp finish

contents.name: Organic Lavender Green
contents.description: 1/4 Lb, Natural bergamot essences & whole organic lavender flowers which has become one of our top sellers. Preparation Organic Lavender Green tea may be served in traditional gaiwan or prepared in a standard full-sized teapot. Allow approximately 3-5 grams of tea per standard sized 6 oz gaiwan (or 3 grams of tea per 10 oz of water if a teapot is used) & cover w/ 70Ã‚Â°C (158Ã‚Â°F) water for 1-2 minutes. This tea may be re-steeped up to four times.

contents.name: Organic Gunpowder
contents.description: Gunpowder is one of the best known & widely drunk green teas in the world. Also known as the green pearl for its pleasing shape & color, our certified organic gunpowder is produced in zhejiang province under strict imo supervision by rolling large, tender leaves into evenly sized little balls which "blossom" under hot water to produce a full, rich & smooth cup of refreshing green tea. Excellent as a hearty breakfast or afternoon tea or served w/ food anytime.

contents.name: Organic Yunnan Mao Feng
contents.description: We discovered this special green tea during our quest for green puerh materials. This unique green tea features a delightful apricot-like fruitiness & a "just right" chewy viscosity that make it memorable. To double up on the bargain, the unique quality of yunnan's green tea makes possible extended aging in dry climates.

contents.name: Organic Dragon Well
contents.description: China's premiere green tea now available in our long-awaited first certified organic dragon well. Beautiful deep green leaves, that famous dragon well aroma & a rich & full-bodied flavor w/ a crisp finish. Vacuum packed for maximum freshness.

contents.name: Organic Cloud Mist
contents.description: Another exciting new organic green tea we're proud to welcome to our green tea collection. Attractively curled deep green leaves produce a sunny golden-yellow infusion w/ a strong green tea flavor & crisp refreshing finish

contents.name: Organic Rooibos
contents.description: The south african herbal drink rooibos is gaining popularity as a caffeine-free substitute for black tea. Like black tea, it can be enjoyed plain or w/ milk & sugar. Our top-quality rooibos is organic & yields a rich, red infusion.

contents.name: Organic Tea Sampler
contents.description: Our organic tea sampler features a crisply unmistakable darjeeling, the robust, bright cup of gunpowder, a hearty English breakfast & an invigoratingly brisk & full-flavored ceylon.

contents.name: Organic Sencha
contents.description: A unique & well-known style of green tea popularized in japan. Sencha's deep green color & distinctively fresh, grassy flavor come from special steam processing during manufacture.

contents.name: Organic English Breakfast
contents.description: A​ crisp & robust certified organic English breakfast style black tea blend. Beautifully complemented by milk & sugar or honey & lemon. Now available in non-organic "silk" pyramid teabags, enjoy full leaf tea w/ the teabag convenience

contents.name: Organic Ceylon
contents.description: An​ invigoratingly brisk & full-flavored certified organic ceylon tea from sri lanka. Delicious on its own or served w/ milk & sugar.

contents.name: New Hunan Dragon's Mane
contents.description: The hunan dragon's mane is expertly (and carefully) pan-fired by hand so that the white "mane" stays intact. The tea then undergoes a gentle firing over charcoal to heighten the aromatics & further reduce moisture.

contents.name: Organic Purple Bamboo
contents.description: Our 2011 organic purple bamboo is sweet, nicely textured, & without a hint of aggressiveness. Brew w/ a mid- to high-temperature range to bring out more flavor. Allow the liquor to cool a bit before drinking to bring out the silky texture.

contents.name: Imperial Ivory Green Tea
contents.description: It's​ not as fresh & grassy as its jade-colored sibling, but instead it offers weighty texture & a sweet, full flavor that would pair delightfully w/ a meal. The leaves become even paler upon infusion, & the liquor is light yellow, belying its rich taste

contents.name: 2012 Harvest Imperial Dragon Well
contents.description: This year's harvest displays a uniquely thicker texture & viscosity, w/ a soft but insistent finish. Due to the rain & cold weather, this year's harvest is extremely limited at less than half of last year's total production.

contents.name: Hunan Lotus Heart
contents.description: Grown & manufactured in Hunan province, this is a true "lotus heart" tea that closely resembles the first-class dragon well from zhejiang but deserves to be appreciated on its own considerable merits. The blade-shaped leaf is amazingly uniform & consists exclusively of buds. This beautiful hunan lotus heart has a buttery mouth-feel & lightly vegetative & delicate yet powerful flavor & aroma

contents.name: 2009 Cui Feng
contents.description: This classic green tea is distinguished by the tufts of fur that jacket each leaf, providing a striking contrast of color & texture, a pleasant viscosity enhanced by the weight of the fur, & intense flavor of fresh green tea boosted by the added texture & maltiness.

contents.name: Organic Lavender Green
contents.description: An especially aromatic & flavorful blend of certified organically produced green tea, natural bergamot essences & whole organic lavender flowers which has become one of our top sellers

contents.name: Dancing Blossoms
contents.description: Tippy, spring-harvested green tea is individually hand-tied into a jade treasure sphere. After infusion, the jade sphere slowly opens into an elegant flower which releases a floating string of beautiful white jasmine flowers to dance & sway in the water of your teapot, as if the flowers are gently swaying in a summer breeze. In this year's tea, the slowly swaying jasmine blossoms are now complimented w/ a lotus of red leaves.

contents.name: Flower of Prosperity
contents.description: Gold & red are the colors of good fortune & prosperity, respectively. This exquisitely hand-tied green tea reveals a string of gold & red blossoms when brewed. A feast for the eye as well as the palate, & the perfect gift.

contents.name: Green Peony
contents.description: Named for the lucky flower of wealth it resembles, this truly unique & beautiful tea is carefully hand-made by experienced tea artisans who select & arrange the choicest large tea buds & tie them w/ a silk thread. The resulting intricate little buds "blossom" when covered w/ hot water & produce a sweet-smelling, pale gold infusion w/ a deliciously smooth & floral, full-bodied flavor which lasts through many infusions

contents.name: Fu Yang Sparrow Tongue Dragon Well
contents.description: It has all of the intensity & complexity expected of a great dragon well. This tea inspires high hopes that the fu yang farm may eventually produce our Imperial dragon well

contents.name: Genmai Cha
contents.description: One​ of our most popular tea selections. The quality of Imperial's Genmai Cha is evident in its dark green color, large, even leaf size, & perfect blend of lightly roasted & popped rice. The flavor of its bright yellow infusion is strong & savory w/ a pleasant aftertaste.

contents.name: Longevity Green
contents.description: This top quality green tea is hand-harvested, allowed to wither indoors for a short time to soften, & then steamed. The steaming arrests any further oxidization (applying heat to tea leaves helps to stop the leaves from oxidizing & turning red). Moistened & softened by steaming, the leaves are then rolled into tightly curled "needles." This process not only makes the leaves more uniform in size & shape, it also allows the tea "juice" to be squeezed out, coating the leaves w/ their own delicious juices. The final process of drying is done by slow-roasting the leaves over a charcoal fire, which at the same time heightens the tea's aromatics. Longevity Green is full-bodied; the mouthfeel is intense, lively, & concentrated, w/ a long & lush finish. The color of the cup is a brilliant yellowish green.

contents.name: Dragon Well
contents.description: High grown in zhejiang province, this year's dragon well is nutty & sweet and, as always, full bodied w/ just the right amount of complexity. Due to weather conditions, this year's harvest is less than half of the usual production.

contents.name: 2012 Harvest: Imperial Lotus Heart Dragon Well
contents.description: Imperial tea court is pleased to present our 2012 lian rui (lotus heart) dragon well, a masterpiece that is truly the highest expression of the teamaster's art. The tiny leaf sets (the tea plant's first production of spring, during a brief break from foul weather), each consist of a single leaf & an unopened bud, & have been hand-sorted for breathtaking uniformity, giving the tea an exquisite visual presentation.

contents.name: Valentine Rose
contents.description: We've saved this special tea just for this special day of the heart. Valentine rose is a perfect-sized & exquisitely hand-tied heart of green tea, representing the force of life. Within the heart is a white chrysanthemum, representing purity, & enclosed within the heart of the chrysanthemum is a red rose, representing passion & romance. When infused in hot water, all three elements are revealed one by one. Your valentine will not only find the tea charming but delicious as well.

contents.name: Osmanthus Dragon Well
contents.description: The osmanthus flower (osmanthus fragrans) is native to southern china & highly prized for its uniquely fragrant, fruity-floral blossoms. It is used in the production of costly perfumes & here as a complement to one of china's best known & most popular green teas. The distinctive fragrance of osmanthus beautifully accents the rich, smooth flavor of dragon well for a deliciously full-bodied cup that is memorably sweet & floral. An excellent green tea for any time of day

contents.description: The 2011 production is uniform & tippy w/ more of that unmistakable & delightfully thick silky viscosity. It's a one-of-a-kind tea full of deliciously complex spring flavors.

contents.name: Rose Garden Dragon Well
contents.description: A combination of two of the world's favorite flavors: the rich chestnut-like taste & rounded mouth-feel of premium dragon well wedded to the floral aroma & pungent sweetness of rose petals. Decadent or imperial

contents.name: Yunnan Spring Tips
contents.description: This big tip green tea is surprisingly gentle w/ a slight hint of interesting astringency. Distinctive fruity aromatics intertwine w/ traces of mild smokiness. The golden yellow brew provides a Lush velvety mouth feel & a long & unforgettable finish.

contents.name: Mountaineer's Green Tea Chai
contents.description: 1/4​ Lb, formulated w/ herbs & spices to resemble the spiced green tea used by china's southwestern highlanders, imperial tea court's mountaineer's green tea chai is strong & bold, perfectly suited to be enjoyed w/ milk & sugar or paired w/ strong or spicy foods.

contents.name: Organic Sencha
contents.description: A unique & well-known style of green tea popularized in Japan. Sencha's deep green color & distinctively fresh, grassy flavor come from special steam processing during manufacture.

contents.name: Gunpowder
contents.description: One of the best known & most widely consumed green teas in the world. Also known as the green pearl for its pleasing shape & color, the best gunpowder is produced in zhejiang province by rolling large, tender leaves into evenly sized little balls which blossom under hot water to produce a full-flavored, refreshingly astringent infusion w/ a hint of smokiness.

contents.name: Sword of the Emperor
contents.description: The springy, long & tightly rolled leaf is beautiful & consists only of large, down-covered buds. Its liquor has a light but distinct aroma & a flavor that combines fruity sweetness w/ a dry, vegetative character. Together these set off a commotion on the palate that is somehow like drinking chinese preserved plums, & these exhilarating taste sensations taper off to a long finish.

contents.name: Valentine Rose
contents.description: We've saved this special tea just for this special day of the heart. Valentine Rose is a perfect-sized & exquisitely hand-tied heart of green tea, representing the force of life. Within the heart is a white chrysanthemum, representing purity, & enclosed within the heart of the chrysanthemum is a red rose, representing passion & romance. When infused in hot water, all three elements are revealed one by one.

contents.name: Green Tea Ginger Ginseng
contents.description: 1/4 lb, the green tea supplies antioxidants while the ginger & ginseng help support a healthy immune system. Other fine herbs add depth & balance to this healthful herbal tonic. It is stimulating & delicious morning or afternoon, hot or iced & sweetened w/ honey.

contents.name: Lychee Blossoms
contents.description: A new addition to our flower tea collection, this beauty features a red lychee flower waiting to blossom inside a surrounding flower of green tea. Subtly scented w/ jasmine & flavored w/ lychee fruit, this stunning tea will display beautifully in a glass teapot

contents.name: Superior White Peony
contents.description: Superior white peony displays a sweet, mellow, & slightly fruity flavor profile, & a shimmering honey-gold infusion. A velveteen mouth feel yields to a long & surprisingly complex finish

contents.name: Imperial Silver Needle Jasmine
contents.description: Since white teas are mild in flavor, including a small amount of young leaves during harvesting ensures adequate tea flavor after scenting w/ jasmine flowers. White teas are excellent candidates for scenting, as their downy leaves attract & retain aromatics.

contents.name: Imperial White Peony
contents.description: A typical white peony is produced as a leaf set containing two leaves & a bud. But the white tip is furry & the two green leaves still retain their early spring white down on the bottom of the leaves.

contents.name: Imperial Silver Needles
contents.description: The imperial silver needles has a really fresh smell & taste.

contents.name: Imperial White Peony & Rose Petals
contents.description: Classic white peony tea is made from downy buds that have two small leaves attached to their base (termed two leaves & a bud). The two leaves cradling the bud are said to resemble the shape of peony flower petals. Our imperial white peony w/ rose is made from specially produced fujian white tea generously blended w/ the finest dried rose petals.

contents.name: China White w/ Chrysanthemum
contents.description: The smooth, distinctive taste of superior quality white tea from fujian province is beautifully combined w/ the full, sweet flavor of dried chrysanthemum blossoms. An attractive & unique treat for teatime anytime.

contents.name: Jun Shan Yin Zhen
contents.description: 1 oz sampler, the unopened leaf- buds, tender & covered w/ white hair, are quickly de-enzymed by heat & then heaped & left covered w/ mats, a step which induces the tea's bio-chemical transformation not oxidation & produces the leaf's characteristic pale gold color. After a final shaping & firing, junshan yinzhen offers an intriguing flavor, somehow deeper & fruitier than green tea, w/ abundant hints of smoke & an ethereally sweet finish

contents.name: Huoshan Huang Ya
contents.description: Large​ lovingly hand-crafted leaves & downy silver buds make up this attractive "yellow bud" tea of anhui province. A fascinating product notable for the deeply floral character of its infusion. Rich, full & smooth, green tea drinkers will appreciate the opportunity to sample this rare treasure.
